Geocode Incidents

#geocode incidents for lat long

geocode_incident <- function(df)
{
  #create columns for lat/long
  df$lat <- as.numeric(0)
  df$long <- as.numeric(0)
  
  #loop through dataframe and geocode each location
  for(i in 1:nrow(df))
  {
    loc <- df[i,]$LOCATION
    lat_lon <- geocode(loc, output = "latlon", source = "google")
    df[i,]$lat <- lat_lon$lat
    df[i,]$long <- lat_lon$lon
  }
  
  return(df)
}

incidents_geocoded <- geocode_incident(incidents)

Plot Incidents with ggmap

my_loc <- c(lon = -80.8431, lat = 35.2271)

map <- get_map(location=my_loc, 
               source = "google", 
               maptype = "roadmap", 
               zoom = 10 ) 
## Map from URL : http://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/staticmap?center=35.2271,-80.8431&zoom=10&size=640x640&scale=2&maptype=roadmap&language=en-EN&sensor=false
ggmap(map) + geom_point(aes(x = long, y = lat), data = incidents_geocoded, color = "darkred" )

Plot incidents with leaflet

m <- leaflet(data = incidents_geocoded) %>%  
  addTiles() %>% 
  setView(lng = -80.8431, lat = 35.2271, zoom = 12) %>%
  addMarkers(~long, ~lat, popup = ~as.character(NARRATIVE))


m
